 FOOTBALL lovers can look forward to more international football action on DStv and GOtv, as the group  of the 2020/21 UEFA Nations League   as well as  the UEFA Euro Qualifiers 2020 and international friendly matches  to be screened on  SuperSport. From today , SuperSport will provide coverage on no less than 10 international friendlies and no less than 32 UEFA Nations League (UNL) and Euro 2020 matches in the space of seven days. Today’s  International Friendlies is headlined by a British derby between England and Wales where Three Lions’ Everton striker Dominic Calvert-Lewin will be hoping to make a major impact on his first call-up to Gareth Southgate’s team. Elsewhere,  Belgium and New Zealand kick-off at 7:45pm on SuperSport Premier League while Russia and Sweden battle it out  earlier at 5:30pm on SuperSport Premier League. Meanwhile, Euro 2020 qualification has reached the playoff semifinal stage with the match between  Georgia and Belarus at 5pm today  on SS Premiere League. The  Scotland tie against  Israel will be aired at 7:45pm on SS Football while Slovakia vs  Republic of Ireland ; Northern Ireland vs  Bosnia and Herzegovina will both  be shown  be shown at 7:45pm on SS Variety 3 and SS La Liga respectively. Similarly, the UNL action gets underway on Saturday 10 October, with the pick of the games seeing Spain host Switzerland at 7:45pm on SS Premier League.